result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Michael P Coupe was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Michael P Coupe is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Michael P Coupe was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Deferred Judgment Agreement

Defendant Michael P Coupe in court with attorney John E Voorhees.   Jodie Bednar-Clemens appeared for the State of Wisconsin. This case is being held in Oneida County. Called at 11:18 AM. Bednar- resolved - plead to count #5 and #6 as alleged; on #5 - deferred entry of judgment for 1 year, terms contained in the agreement, no possession or consumption of any drugs unless prescribed to him, 50 hours of community srevice, no bond violations, notify FC DA if arrested for any crime, notify FC DA for change of address and phone number, plead to count #6 as alleged and costs only. Counts #1 thru #4 have already been dismissed. Court dismisses counts #1 thru #4 if they have not yet been dismissed. Vorhees pleads NC to count #5 as alleged and to #6 as alleged. Coupe agrees. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges G on count #6 and withholds finding of guilt on count #5, accepts deferred entry of judgment on that count. Bednar - nothing further. Voorhees - makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation - asks that bond be applied to the costs on count #6 and set a signature bond. Coupe withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following: count #6 - costs including DNA surcharge - take bond posted, refund remainder, set for review hearing in 1 year on count #5, right to appeal, sets bond at $1000 signature bond. Adjourned at 11:29 PM.
